<br>
Just my take on the subject...<br>
<br>
Any guild that is comfortable enough to declare themselves &quot;Free For All&quot; won't care if they are blacklisted. They will have their own resources to deal with ports, rezzes etc. Yes, their members will find it a little more difficult, but frankly most of these guilds that declare themselves FFA simply group with themselves and take care of their own anyway. So being &quot;blacklisted&quot; really means very little to them.<br>
<br>
The only negative thing FFA guilds seem to suffer is they won't be able to recruit &quot;nice&quot; players. On most servers this isnt an issue because there are always people that play that just want to do the high end raids, grab the uber loot and could really care less about the negatives associated with their guildtags.<br>
<br>
I doubt that will happen here on FV because of a couple of things. First there are already two large guilds that have made arrangememts to deal with planes and other mobs. I am sure as other guilds grow in strength and power they would be more than willing to work with them. Baku and Coinfist both seem like reasonable people and thier posts certainly seem to reflect that.<br>
<br>
Second, the population of this server isn't going to create an atmosphere of intense competition for high end mobs. Its this intense competition that usually creates all the problems which ultimately leads to a guild declaring itself FFA.<br>
<br>
Anyways, thats my take on the whole thing. Lemme know what ya think.<br>
<br>
**edit**<br>
<br>
For those that think mobs like Tunare and such won't be dropped on this server I would have to disagree. Its just going to be a matter of time. Most mobs in this game can be done with 40 people or less and there are two high end guilds that already have those numbers, they are just building up the levels and gear.<br>
<br>
<br>
