<br>
Yes, Raistlin was often mistrusted and rightfully so for in the end it was revealed that he was only using the group to further his own purpose--the acquisition of power.  He especially used his brother, Caramon, without who's strength he would have perished any number of times.  <br>
<br>
However, I think it was more Raistlin's cold-blooded cynicism (pragmatism?) that bothered the companions so much.  Afterall, he seldomly did anything that was out-and-out harmful to the group, and very often saved them with his magic. <p><b>Tresjoli Louveteau</b>
